PART III: THE TWO-BODY vs MANY-BODY COMPETITION
========================================================================

  p=7:
    Max IPR = 0.3611: σ = (-1, 1, -1), H = 175
    Min IPR = 0.1667: σ = (-1, -1, 1), H = 189
    H(max IPR) / H(min IPR) = 0.925926
    → LOW IPR WINS (Schur-concave direction)

  p=11:
    Max IPR = 0.3444: σ = (1, -1, 1, -1, 1), H = 93027
    Min IPR = 0.1000: σ = (1, -1, 1, 1, 1), H = 95095
    H(max IPR) / H(min IPR) = 0.978253
    → LOW IPR WINS (Schur-concave direction)

  p=13:
    Max IPR = 0.3413: σ = (1, -1, 1, -1, -1, 1), H = 3711175
    Min IPR = 0.1054: σ = (-1, 1, -1, 1, 1, 1), H = 3703011
    H(max IPR) / H(min IPR) = 1.002205
    → HIGH IPR WINS (Schur-convex direction)

